<section>
    <h2>Lab Introduction</h2>
    <p>
        This lab introduces basic concepts of data handling and data visualization.
        Graphical representations help in understanding data distribution, spread,
        and central tendency.
    </p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Histogram</h2>
    <p>
        A histogram represents frequency distribution using continuous bars.
    </p>

    <div class="chart">
        <svg width="400" height="200">
            <rect x="40" y="80" width="40" height="100" fill="#2563eb"/>
            <rect x="90" y="40" width="40" height="140" fill="#2563eb"/>
            <rect x="140" y="20" width="40" height="160" fill="#2563eb"/>
            <rect x="190" y="60" width="40" height="120" fill="#2563eb"/>
            <rect x="240" y="100" width="40" height="80" fill="#2563eb"/>
        </svg>
        <p><b>Fig:</b> Histogram</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Skewness</h2>
    <p>
        Skewness indicates asymmetry in a data distribution.
    </p>

    <div class="chart">
        <svg width="400" height="200">
            <path d="M20 160 Q120 20 380 160" fill="none" stroke="#16a34a" stroke-width="3"/>
        </svg>
        <p><b>Fig:</b> Positively Skewed Distribution</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Box Plot</h2>
    <p>
        A box plot shows data distribution using minimum, quartiles, median, and maximum.
    </p>

    <div class="chart">
        <svg width="400" height="120">
            <line x1="50" y1="60" x2="350" y2="60" stroke="black"/>
            <rect x="140" y="40" width="120" height="40" fill="#facc15"/>
            <line x1="200" y1="40" x2="200" y2="80" stroke="black" stroke-width="2"/>
            <line x1="100" y1="60" x2="140" y2="60" stroke="black"/>
            <line x1="260" y1="60" x2="300" y2="60" stroke="black"/>
        </svg>
        <p><b>Fig:</b> Box Plot</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Measures of Central Tendency</h2>
    <p>
        Measures of central tendency describe the center of the data.
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li><b>Mean:</b> Arithmetic average</li>
        <li><b>Median:</b> Middle value</li>
        <li><b>Mode:</b> Most frequent value</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Measures of Dispersion</h2>
    <p>
        Measures of dispersion describe the spread of data.
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Range</li>
        <li>Variance</li>
        <li>Standard Deviation</li>
        <li>Coefficient of Variation</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Conclusion</h2>
    <p>
        Data visualization techniques like histograms and box plots help in
        understanding data distribution clearly. Measures of central tendency and
        dispersion summarize data efficiently.
    </p>
</section>

